    "summary": "Wittgenstein familiarity rating: 3/5",
    "content": "**Wittgenstein familiarity: 3/5**\n\n**Confident handling:**\n- Later Wittgenstein's language games and forms of life, insofar as they intersect with existentialist themes -- particularly the idea that meaning is embedded in practices and ways of living rather than in correspondence to facts. This overlaps with Heidegger's account of world-disclosure and the author's 梦境/境 framework.\n- The \"rule-following\" problem and its connection to existential freedom -- the question of whether following a rule is determined by the rule itself or by the human practice of applying it. This is relevant to the author's account of how 形而上 (metaphysical constructs) function as frameworks for action.\n- Wittgenstein's therapeutic conception of philosophy (\"philosophy leaves everything as it is\") as it relates to the author's post-nihilistic stance -- both reject the idea that philosophy discovers hidden essences and instead focus on clarifying what is already before us.\n\n**Less confident:**\n- The Tractatus's picture theory of meaning and the formal logic apparatus (truth tables, logical atomism). This is far from existentialist territory and I would not claim expertise.\n- The technical details of private language argument, criteria vs. symptoms, and aspect-seeing (seeing-as) -- I know these in outline but not with the precision a Wittgenstein specialist would bring.\n- Formal connections between Wittgenstein's grammar/depth grammar and the author's category-theoretic formalization of linguistic structure in K1策略. This is where my 3/5 really shows its limits."
  }
}
